PACIFIC OCEAN • variety with shallow hydrothecae and long lateral nematothecae: 1 fertile colony, with stems up to 3 cm high; off New Caledonia , stn DW4725; 22°41′ S , 167°05′ E ;
240–256 m
;
20 Aug. 2016
; KANACONO leg.; MNHN-IK-2015-605
.

Monostaechas fisheri

is still a poorly-known, seldomly-recorded species. Speculations on its affinities with 

M. quadridens

often provided inconclusive or cautious opinions (e.g., 
Stechow 1925
; 
Vervoort 1968
; 
Migotto 1996
; 
Schuchert 1997
), although some authors pleaded for a definitive inclusion in its synonymy (e.g., 
Leloup 1937
; 
Watson 2011
).
